overview: "The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The agent performed
  a comprehensive analysis, identifying both implemented features and
  significant gaps. A prioritized plan was created to address these missing
  functionalities. The agent then proceeded to implement the first two
  high-priority items: integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness
  interference, complete with critical safety warnings for high scores, and
  adding logic for detecting and reporting Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea
  (COMISA). This involved modifying data types, validation schemas, the
  questionnaire UI, and both the web and PDF report generation components. The
  implementation ensures that users with severe tiredness receive immediate
  safety advice and that a crucial sleep disorder is explicitly identified."
